name: Hermione Granger
description: Brilliant, logical, and hardworking witch who values knowledge and academic achievement above all else.
analysis: Hermione exemplifies high conscientiousness and openness to experience, with strong intellectual curiosity but lower agreeableness when it comes to rule-breaking. Her personality combines perfectionism with genuine care for others.

name: Sherlock Holmes
description: Brilliant detective with exceptional analytical skills and attention to detail, but lacking in social graces.
analysis: Holmes shows extremely high openness and low agreeableness, with moderate conscientiousness focused on his work. His low extraversion and high neuroticism contribute to his eccentric and sometimes difficult personality.

name: Tony Stark / Iron Man
description: Genius inventor, billionaire, and superhero with a charismatic but sometimes arrogant personality.
analysis: Stark combines extremely high openness and extraversion with moderate conscientiousness. His high neuroticism manifests as anxiety and PTSD, while his agreeableness varies depending on the situation.

name: Atticus Finch
description: Morally upright lawyer who stands for justice and treats all people with dignity and respect.
analysis: Finch exemplifies high agreeableness and conscientiousness with strong moral principles. His moderate extraversion allows him to be both a public figure and private thinker, while low neuroticism provides emotional stability.

name: Elizabeth Bennet
description: Witty, independent, and strong-willed young woman who values authenticity and personal freedom.
analysis: Elizabeth shows high openness to experience and moderate extraversion, with strong principles that sometimes clash with social expectations. Her low neuroticism helps her maintain confidence in challenging situations.

name: Darth Vader
description: Fallen Jedi turned Sith Lord, driven by fear, anger, and a desire for control and power.
analysis: Vader represents extremely high neuroticism and low agreeableness, with high conscientiousness focused on order and control. His fall represents a dramatic personality change from his earlier self.

name: Tyrion Lannister
description: Witty, intelligent dwarf who uses humor and cleverness to navigate a world that often underestimates him.
analysis: Tyrion combines high openness and extraversion with moderate agreeableness that's complicated by family loyalty. His neuroticism varies but intelligence and wit are consistent strengths.

name: Steve Rogers / Captain America
description: Moral leader and super-soldier who embodies traditional American values of courage, honor, and justice.
analysis: Rogers shows extremely high conscientiousness and agreeableness with strong moral convictions. Moderate extraversion makes him a natural leader, while low neuroticism provides emotional stability in crisis.

name: Luna Lovegood
description: Dreamy, eccentric, and kind-hearted witch who sees the world through a unique and magical lens.
analysis: Luna exhibits extremely high openness to experience with unconventional thinking patterns. Her high agreeableness and low neuroticism create a calm, accepting personality that others find both puzzling and comforting.

name: Walter White
description: Chemistry teacher turned drug manufacturer, whose pride and desperation lead him down a dark path.
analysis: Walter's personality transforms throughout his arc, but consistently shows high conscientiousness in his work, increasing neuroticism due to stress, and decreasing agreeableness as he becomes more manipulative.

name: Bruce Wayne / Batman
description: Billionaire vigilante driven by a desire for justice and haunted by childhood trauma.
analysis: Batman shows extremely high conscientiousness and moderate to high neuroticism from trauma. His agreeableness is complicated - low in methods but high in ultimate goals. High openness to unconventional solutions.

name: Gandalf
description: Wise wizard and guide who balances ancient knowledge with compassion for all living beings.
analysis: Gandalf exhibits high openness and agreeableness with wisdom accumulated over millennia. His conscientiousness manifests in long-term planning, while low neuroticism provides the calm needed for leadership.

name: Daenerys Targaryen
description: Dragon queen who evolves from exile to conqueror, driven by a desire to liberate the oppressed.
analysis: Daenerys shows high extraversion and variable agreeableness depending on circumstances. Her conscientiousness grows with responsibility, while neuroticism increases under pressure and trauma.

name: Spock
description: Half-human, half-Vulcan officer who struggles to balance logic with emotion.
analysis: Spock exhibits extremely high conscientiousness and openness to logical analysis, with low extraversion and carefully controlled neuroticism. His agreeableness is filtered through logic rather than emotion.

name: Diana Prince / Wonder Woman
description: Amazonian warrior princess who fights for truth, justice, and compassion in the modern world.
analysis: Wonder Woman combines high agreeableness and conscientiousness with strong moral convictions. Her extraversion makes her a natural leader, while low neuroticism provides emotional strength in battle.
